  "overview": {
    "value": "Agnibaan is a three-stage small-lift orbital launch vehicle of AgniKul Cosmos, currently under development, 18 metres tall with a 1.3-metre diameter and a lift-off mass of 14,000 kg. It is capable of placing a 100 kg satellite into a 700 km orbit. Its suborbital single-stage technology demonstrator, Agnibaan SOrTeD, flew successfully on 30 May 2024, but as stated in the article, no orbital rocket was launched in 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025.",
